article.headline: Portland St. 107, Pacific Lutheran 57
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Dupree Lucas scored 19 points to lead Portland State to a 107-57 victory over Pacific Lutheran on Thursday night. Scott Morrison scored 17 points and grabbed six rebounds for the Vikings (6-3), who have won five of their last six games. Deonte Huff added 15 points for PSU, which topped the 100-point mark for the first time since the 1999-2000 season. Josh Vanlandingham led PLU with 11 points and was the only Lute player to reach double figures. Portland State out-manned the Division III Lutes all night. The Vikings led by as many as 22 points in the first half and held a 48-28 advantage at halftime. The Lutes got no closer than 17 points the rest of the game. The bigger Vikings dominated the Lutes down low, outrebounding PLU 54-35 and racking up a 52-24 advantage in the paint. Pacific Lutheran shot just 30 percent from the field while PSU connected on 50 percent for the night.
